MOST EXPECTED VIVA Q&A (1-LINE ANSWERS)
🔹 ER Model & Design
What is ER model? → It is a conceptual design showing entities and relationships.
What is an entity? → A real-world object stored in database.
What is an attribute? → Property of an entity.
What is a relationship? → Association between entities.
What is primary key? → Unique identifier of a record.
🔹 Relational Model
What is a relation? → Table in relational database.
What is tuple? → Row in a table.
What is attribute? → Column in a table.
What is domain? → Set of valid values for a column.
What is foreign key? → Attribute referencing primary key of another table.
🔹 Normalization
What is normalization? → Process of removing redundancy.
What is 1NF? → Removes repeating groups.
What is 2NF? → Removes partial dependency.
What is 3NF? → Removes transitive dependency.
What is anomaly? → Problem in data operations.
🔹 DDL Commands
What is DDL? → Commands to define structure.
What is CREATE? → Creates table.
What is ALTER? → Modifies table structure.
What is DROP? → Deletes table permanently.
What is TRUNCATE? → Deletes all rows but keeps structure.
🔹 DML Commands
What is DML? → Commands to manipulate data.
What is INSERT? → Adds data into table.
What is SELECT? → Retrieves data.
What is UPDATE? → Modifies data.
What is DELETE? → Removes data.
🔹 SQL Querying
What is JOIN? → Combines data from multiple tables.
Types of JOIN? → INNER, LEFT, RIGHT, FULL.
What is ANY? → Checks if any value matches condition.
What is ALL? → Checks if all values satisfy condition.
What is UNION? → Combines results without duplicates.
What is INTERSECT? → Returns common rows.
What are constraints? → Rules to maintain data integrity.
🔹 Subqueries
What is subquery? → Query inside another query.
What is nested subquery? → Executes once.
What is correlated subquery? → Executes for each row.
What is EXISTS? → Checks if subquery returns rows.
🔹 Aggregate & Views
What is aggregate function? → Function on multiple rows.
Examples? → COUNT, SUM, AVG, MAX, MIN.
What is GROUP BY? → Groups rows.
What is HAVING? → Filters grouped data.
What is view? → Virtual table.
Why use view? → To simplify complex queries.
🔹 Triggers
What is trigger? → Auto-executed SQL block.
Types of triggers? → INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE.
What is :NEW? → New value of row.
What is :OLD? → Old value of row.
BEFORE vs AFTER trigger? → BEFORE validates, AFTER logs.
🔹 Procedures
What is procedure? → Stored SQL block.
Advantage? → Reusability and performance.
How to execute? → Using EXEC command.
What are parameters? → Inputs to procedure.
🔹 Cursors
What is cursor? → Row-by-row processing tool.
Steps in cursor? → Declare, Open, Fetch, Close.
What is %NOTFOUND? → Checks no more rows.
Why use cursor? → To process multiple rows individually.









ADVANCED VIVA Q&A (1-LINE ANSWERS)
🔹 Keys & Constraints
What is candidate key? → Minimal set of attributes that uniquely identify a tuple.
What is super key? → Set of attributes that uniquely identify a tuple (may have extra attributes).
What is alternate key? → Candidate key not chosen as primary key.
What is composite key? → Key with more than one attribute.
What is NOT NULL constraint? → Ensures column cannot have NULL values.
What is UNIQUE constraint? → Ensures all values are different.
What is CHECK constraint? → Restricts values based on condition.
What is DEFAULT constraint? → Assigns default value if none provided.
🔹 Normalization (Advanced)
What is functional dependency? → Relationship between attributes.
What is partial dependency? → Dependency on part of composite key.
What is transitive dependency? → Indirect dependency via another attribute.
What is BCNF? → Stronger version of 3NF.
Why normalization? → To reduce redundancy and anomalies.
🔹 SQL Querying (Advanced)
Difference between WHERE and HAVING? → WHERE filters rows, HAVING filters groups.
Difference between UNION and UNION ALL? → UNION removes duplicates, UNION ALL keeps duplicates.
What is CROSS JOIN? → Cartesian product of two tables.
What is SELF JOIN? → Table joined with itself.
What is NATURAL JOIN? → Automatically joins common columns.
What is subquery in FROM clause? → Inline view.
🔹 Subqueries (Advanced)
What is scalar subquery? → Returns single value.
What is multi-row subquery? → Returns multiple rows.
IN vs EXISTS? → IN compares values, EXISTS checks presence.
ANY vs ALL difference? → ANY checks one, ALL checks all.
🔹 Aggregate & Views
Can HAVING be used without GROUP BY? → Yes, but rarely used.
What is difference between COUNT() and COUNT(column)? → COUNT() counts all rows, COUNT(column) ignores NULLs.
What is materialized view? → Physically stored view.
Can we update a view? → Yes, if it is simple view.
🔹 Triggers (Advanced)
What is row-level trigger? → Executes for each row.
What is statement-level trigger? → Executes once per statement.
Can we have multiple triggers? → Yes, on same table.
What is trigger event? → INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE operation.
Why use trigger? → For automation and validation.
🔹 Procedures (Advanced)
Difference between procedure and function? → Function returns value, procedure may not.
What is IN parameter? → Input parameter.
What is OUT parameter? → Output parameter.
What is INOUT parameter? → Both input and output.
🔹 Cursors (Advanced)
What is implicit cursor? → Automatically created by DBMS.
What is explicit cursor? → Created by user.
What is cursor attribute? → %FOUND, %NOTFOUND, %ROWCOUNT.
What is %ROWCOUNT? → Number of rows processed.
🔹 Transactions & Misc
What is transaction? → Group of SQL operations.
What is COMMIT? → Saves changes permanently.
What is ROLLBACK? → Undo changes.
What is SAVEPOINT? → Temporary point in transaction.
What is ACID property? → Atomicity, Consistency, Isolation, Durability.
🔹 Common Differences (Very Important)
DELETE vs TRUNCATE? → DELETE removes rows with condition, TRUNCATE removes all quickly.
DROP vs TRUNCATE? → DROP removes table, TRUNCATE removes data.
JOIN vs UNION? → JOIN combines columns, UNION combines rows.
Trigger vs Procedure? → Trigger auto, procedure manual.
Cursor vs Loop? → Cursor processes rows from query.













